message.content: cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB. The paper discusses information retrieval for Points of Interest (POI) and introduces a new dataset for semantically enriching POIs from unstructured data to support open-domain search and question answering. The paper also evaluates the performance of a Lucene-based baseline model and a sentence embedding-based model, which are common techniques in the fields of information retrieval (IR), natural language processing (NLP), and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the performance of the models, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the storage and retrieval of data, which is relevant to cs.DB (Databases).
